---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="How NGOs Can Use Data Analytics for Better Decision Making | Etacom Technology" description="Development organizations collect vast amounts of data but often struggle to turn it into actionable insights.">
  <Header homeLink="/" />

  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero-bg"></div>
      <div class="container page-hero-content">
        <a href="/blog" class="blog-back">&larr; Back to Blog</a>
        <span class="blog-category">AI & Data</span>
        <h1 class="page-hero-title">How NGOs Can Use Data Analytics for Better Decision Making</h1>
        <p class="page-hero-desc">May 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container blog-content">
        <p>Development organizations collect vast amounts of data — beneficiary records, program outcomes, financial reports, field surveys. But often, this data sits in spreadsheets and databases without being fully utilized.</p>

        <h2>The Data Challenge</h2>
        <p>Many NGOs have data but lack the tools and processes to turn it into actionable insights. Reports are manually compiled, taking days or weeks. By the time the data is analyzed, the window for decision-making may have already closed.</p>

        <h2>Building a Data Pipeline</h2>
        <p>A solid data pipeline automates the flow from collection to analysis. Data from field offices, mobile apps, and databases is cleaned, transformed, and loaded into a centralized warehouse where it can be queried and visualized.</p>

        <h2>Visual Dashboards</h2>
        <p>Interactive dashboards give program managers real-time visibility into key metrics — beneficiary reach, budget utilization, program completion rates. Tools like Power BI, Metabase, or custom dashboards make this accessible to non-technical staff.</p>

        <h2>Practical Steps</h2>
        <p>Start small: identify the one report that takes the longest to produce, and automate it. Then expand to other metrics. The goal is not to build a perfect system overnight, but to create a culture of data-driven decision making.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero { position: relative; padding: 140px 0 80px; overflow: hidden; }
  .page-hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: var(--dark); }
  .page-hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .page-hero-title { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 800; color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .page-hero-desc { font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }
  .blog-back { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.875rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 16px; transition: color 0.2s; }
  .blog-back:hover { color: var(--white); }
  .blog-category { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--primary); background: rgba(220,38,38,0.1); padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 50px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .blog-content { max-width: 720px; }
  .blog-content h2 { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--dark); margin: 32px 0 12px; }
  .blog-content p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 16px; }
</style>
